# wp-content baking strategy:
# - Bake plugins/ (except jti-custom — see below), themes/, languages/,
#   mu-plugins/, litespeed/, jetpack-waf/
# - Exclude user uploads (mounted from Azure Files at runtime)
# - Exclude jti-custom — it lives in its own repo and is deployed directly
#   to /persist/plugins/jti-custom/ by its own GH Actions workflow, then
#   pulled into wp-content by the polling overlay. See infra/RUNBOOK.md §5.1.
# - Exclude runtime/cache directories that shouldn't ship in the image
wordpress/wp-content/uploads
wordpress/wp-content/uploads2
wordpress/wp-content/updraft
wordpress/wp-content/plugins-old
wordpress/wp-content/upgrade
wordpress/wp-content/upgrade-temp-backup
# Dev workspace for jti-custom (the active plugin used to live at
# plugins/jti-custom/, but is now deployed separately — see above).
wordpress/wp-content/jti-custom
wordpress/wp-content/plugins/jti-custom
wordpress/wp-content/debug.log
wordpress/wp-content/**/*.log
wordpress/wp-content/**/.DS_Store

# Other things that shouldn't be in the build context
.git
.DS_Store
*.sql
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
docker-compose.yml
.env
.env.example
REVERT-PERF-EXPERIMENT.md

# IaC lives in the same repo but isn't needed inside the runtime image.
# infra/.terraform alone is ~250 MB of provider plugins; including the tree
# adds minutes to az acr build's upload and risks 'Connection aborted' errors.
infra/

# Backup/scratch files — must not be baked into the image
wordpress/**/*.old
wordpress/**/*.bk
wordpress/**/*_bk_before_*
wordpress/wp-config.php.old
wordpress/.htaccess.bk
wordpress/.htaccess_bk_before_multisite
wordpress/dcbf3b82baf921901d2c93b269508e88.txt
